# =============================================================================
# TEAM DEFINITIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES
# =============================================================================

# Core Teams (GitHub teams should be created to match these)
# @q-ecosystem-team - Overall ecosystem oversight
# @documentation-team - Documentation standards and quality
# @technical-writers - Writing quality and style
# @product-team - Product strategy and vision
# @architecture-team - Technical architecture decisions
# @security-team - Security and privacy oversight
# @devops-team - Deployment and operations
# @integration-team - Cross-module integration
# @automation-team - Tooling and automation
# @quality-team - Quality assurance and validation

# Module Teams
# @squid-team - sQuid identity module
# @qwallet-team - Qwallet payment module
# @qmarket-team - Qmarket marketplace module
# @qmail-team - Qmail messaging module
# @qchat-team - Qchat communication module
# @qdrive-team - Qdrive storage module
# @qpic-team - QpiC media module
# @qindex-team - Qindex search module
# @qlock-team - Qlock scheduling module
# @qonsent-team - Qonsent consent module
# @qnet-team - QNET networking module
# @qerberos-team - Qerberos security module
# @qmask-team - Qmask privacy module
# @dao-team - DAO governance module

# Specialized Teams
# @content-team - Video and marketing content
# @marketing-team - Marketing and communications
# @community-team - Community management
# @support-team - User support and troubleshooting
# @testing-team - Testing and QA
# @compliance-team - Legal and compliance
# @legal-team - Legal review
# @executive-team - Executive oversight

# =============================================================================
# REVIEW REQUIREMENTS
# =============================================================================

# Critical documentation requires multiple approvals
/docs/STYLEGUIDE.md @documentation-team @technical-writers @product-team
/docs/GLOSSARY.md @documentation-team @product-team @architecture-team
/docs/CONTRIBUTING.md @documentation-team @community-team @product-team

# Global architecture documentation requires architecture team approval
/docs/global/architecture/ @architecture-team @technical-leads @product-team

# Security documentation requires security team approval
/docs/modules/*/security.md @security-team @module-owners @compliance-team
/docs/global/security/ @security-team @architecture-team @compliance-team

# API documentation requires API team and module owner approval
/docs/modules/*/api-reference.md @api-team @module-owners @integration-team

# =============================================================================
# EMERGENCY CONTACTS
# =============================================================================

# For urgent documentation issues that require immediate attention:
# - Critical security documentation: @security-team @emergency-response
# - Production deployment docs: @devops-team @infrastructure-team @emergency-response
# - Legal/compliance issues: @legal-team @compliance-team @executive-team

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================

# 1. All teams referenced in this file should exist as GitHub teams
# 2. Individual usernames can be used if teams are not available
# 3. At least one code owner must approve changes to owned files
# 4. Code owners are automatically requested for review
# 5. This file itself requires documentation team approval for changes

